name: Gia gelato & cafe
comment: You have to be a paying customer but it's cheap and delicious food so you can get just a glass of water.

name: VIP
directions: Past the "Pick up here" sign, follow the line on the floor all the way to the back. It's on the left.

name: Coffee on the Point
directions: near the back of the shop, behind an art wall
comment: everyone here is really kind and the food is delicious so i recommend buying something if you can, but i doubt they’ll be rude if you go to use it without buying something :)

name: Walmart Neighborhood Market
directions: In and to the right!

name: Poulsbo Maritime Museum
directions: Straight back, on the left.
comment: Free admission

name: Mendocino County Library
directions: Walk in, and right by the front desk is the bathrooms and water fountains.
comment: If you have trouble ask the staff. I forgot their name, but one of the staff is trans.

name: Otter Burger
directions: At the back beyond bar

name: Piedmont Grocery
directions: Go all the way down aisle 6 and turn left.

name: LGBT+ Center of Raleigh
directions: Down the stairs outside, at door make a right, go left, at wall go right, at end of hall go left, two bathrooms— one has two stalls and baby station, the other has one stall and two urinals.
comment: The LGBT+ Center is awesome!

name: Pho Vina
comment: Paying customers only

name: Sogno di Vino
comment: Paying customers only

name: Iris Optikko
directions: Ask staff at iris Optikko
comment: Vessapassi (bathroom pass)

name: Studio C!
directions: Immediately to the right of concessions, labeled "Family Room"
comment: Movie theater - may need to be paying customer

name: Sleepwalker Spirits and Ale
directions: Back of the bar
comment: Two gender-neutral restrooms

name: Chipotle Mexican Grill
comment: No code needed to access the bathrooms!

name: The Cracker Barrel Store
directions: Restroom is past the cashier around the corner on the right.
comment: The store has no stairs to get in and has double doors so should be ok for any wheelchairs to get into the store.  The doors aren’t automatic.  The bathroom is a single stall and pretty small—isn’t handicap friendly size.  I added it in case it would help in a pinch—there aren’t any gas stations right here.

name: TU Berlin MAR Building
directions: second floor
comment: mon-sam 8-20

name: Albertsons
directions: Back left of the store to the right of the gendered bathrooms down the hall a bit.
comment: I wasn’t able to into the bathroom so I’m not sure if there is a changing table or not. I just know the bathroom itself exists

name: Meijer
directions: A part of the front wall when you walk in, next to Ben’s Pretelz
comment: No trash can, but it does have the place to dispose of sanitary products.

name: Sno-Isle Mill Creek Library
directions: Come in front doors turn left. Two unisex bathrooms. Lock door.

name: IHOP
directions: in the back

name: Lane Community College Florence Center
directions: It'll be in the building on the right when you enter the parking lot. Once you enter, it'll be on your left and right before you get to the door that leads to the other building, the bathroom will be on your left.
comment: Just act like you're a student. Blend in. Most students here are usually in their teens through 20's or really old people. There's not much in between.

name: Starbucks
directions: Towards the back past the pastry case.
comment: Purchase appreciated but not required. Sometimes there's a line since it is a single occupancy facility.

name: Smart &Final
directions: Back of right side of store past dairy

name: Johns Hopkins Outpatient Center
directions: Enter through the front sliding door on the ground floor. Take an immediate left, before the Information Desk. The restrooms are on the right of the hallway with the sign "Internal Medicine" above the archway. (NOT through the door.)
comment:
4 restrooms, two small and two accessible.
Other single-stall GNRs scattered throughout the building.

name: Starbucks
directions: Towards the back of the store, past the pastry case. Purchases appreciated but not required.
comment: Single occupancy, sometimes there's a line of people waiting to use it.

name: Rise Biscuits & Donuts
directions: One restroom located in back of restaurant.

name: Arc's Value Village
comment: Two gender-neutral single-user restrooms.

name: Bibles for Missions Thrift Center
directions: in the back
comment: This thrift store is run by a religious organization and I don't know what their official view of LGBTIQ+ people is, but for what it's worth I've never had a problem there.

name: Total Wine & More
directions: in the back
comment: Two single stall restrooms, both gender neutral as of December 2019.

name: Gunther Tooties
directions: To the right, past the counter, left of the stairs. Marked as “all gender restroom”
comment: Not handicap accessible

name: T-Swirl Crepe
directions: In very back of store
comment: You probably have to be a paying customer

name: Hakata Ramen
directions: There is a sign pointing to them in the direction of the waiting area.
comment: You have to be a restaurant patron.

name: Labor and Industry Building
directions: Walk to the center of the first floor lobby and face the elevators; there is an all gender restroom to the left that is also accessible.
comment: No need to interact with anyone, this building is open to the public Monday - Friday

name: Rush Bowls
directions: Suite 105. Limited parking. Best to park next door at Zaxby's and walk over.

name: Tony’s Pizza
directions: In the back past the bar

name: Withcott bus interchange
directions: small independent tin building, right next to the highway
comment: On the map this is marked as the old CWA hall, this was ripped down a few years ago

name: Booth Library
directions:
Stair-free route to the restrooms:

Use south entrance - entrance closest to Coleman Hall
Ride the elevator to the left of the stairs from the South Lobby to floor 3 (3000 Level)
Proceed through the 3000 Level to the central elevator
Ride the central elevator to 4
Proceed through the 4000 Level along the main corridor toward the South Reading Room
Open the door marked “4500-4515.” This is the last door on the right.
The gender inclusive restrooms are between room 4515 and 4510 on the left side of the hallway

name: Jolley Swanton
directions: Immediately in front of entrance door

name: Le Cafe Gourmet
directions: Toward the back of the cafe.
comment: Best authentic French cafe.

name: Jiffy Lube
directions: To the left of the front desk
comment: There's parking spaces and a door leading to the front desk area, so you can get to it without being a customer.

name: Barrie CHC
directions: First or second floor, both floors have bathrooms on left side of building, elevator to second floor.
comment: First floor and second floor have privately stalled bathrooms!

name: Boba Guys San Ramon
directions: To the left side of the store towards the back.
comment: Don’t need to be customer but recommended.

name: City Center San Ramon
directions: To the left of Sephora, down the hallway past concierge, there is a family/nursing room with attached restrooms.

name: Schleman Hall - LGBTQ Center
directions: On the second floor, room 246. Right down the hall from the LGBTQ Center.
comment: The building is only open during regular business hours. Do not have to be a Purdue student, staff, or faculty. All stalls, no urinals. There are gendered restrooms on the first floor as well that should include directions to the gender neutral ones via signage.

name: BLōFISH Clothing Co.
directions: Straight through the front door to the back.

name: St James Infirmary
directions: to the left when you exit elevator on 4th floor. Key is available at the Reception desk or ring the doorbell if after hours.
comment: You need a key from the reception or Drop-in room staff to enter. 2 multi-stall bathrooms. One Bathroom has urinals and two stalls, the other does not have urinals and five stalls.

name: Carson Hall
directions: In the hallways on the 2nd and 3rd floors.
comment: The hallway doors may be locked at night.

name: Carpenter Hall
directions: Lower level

name: Bartlett Hall
directions: First floor. When coming in through the front doors, it will be right on the opposite wall.
comment: Publicly accessible.

name: Black Squirl Cafe
directions: Basement at the back of the shop.
comment: Bathrooms are trans and non-binary friendly. And staff are friendly and helpful too.

name: St. Patrick's Building
directions: Fourth floor, exsit elevator and turn left down long hallway, at the end of the hall make a left, bathroom on your left.
comment: If your on the Carleton University campus this is the only all gender bathroom on campus this far.

name: Dane County Regional Airport
directions: After security check point. Between gates 10 and 11
comment: Also has sharps waste container.

name: Mobil/McDonald's
directions: between the gas station and McDonald's

name: Ottawa Public Library - Ruth E Dickinson
directions: First floor. Beside the men's room and the water fountain. Across the room from the front desk.
comment: Bathroom has a button to lock the door for individuals using a wheelchair.

name: Ruth E Dickinson Library
directions: First floor across from the front desk. Beside the water fountain.

name: First Watch
directions: Go in, walk straight back, around the corner

name: Starbucks
directions: Take an immediate right when you come in the door.
comment: Bathrooms have no code/lock

name: Catonsville Presbyterian Church
directions: First floor, between santuary and kitchen.
comment:
Only open on Sundays 8-
:45-12:30ish

name: Pulkovo Airport
directions: Ground floor, near the "Arrival 2" the is a bathroom for disabled people between gendered ones.

name: Dana Cafe
directions: At the back there is a single unisex toilet.
comment: You probably have to be a playing customer.

name: Kati Vegan Thai
comment: Restrooms are customers only, might be able to ask if they’re slow as staff is very friendly.

name: Cured/18th and 21st
comment: Paying customers. Very trans friendly staff!

name: Subway
directions: On the back wall in the right corner of the restaurant.

name: Pazze e Pizze
directions: at the toilets, you can see them when you walk it
comment: you have to eat here to go to the toilet

name: Crol & Co
directions: Second on the right down the hall
comment: I work here and am transgender. It's a single bathroom with a sanitary waste bin. The cafe is also a safe space :)

name: Garbanzo Mediterranean Fresh
comment: Their bathroom signs specifically embrace nonbinary/trans folx: each sign has a male figure, a female figure, and one that shows 1/2 and 1/2.

name: The Mitten Brewing Company
directions: The accessible bathroom is in the bar area and the gender neutral restrooms are at the front entrance. It seemed like a very welcoming atmosphere.

name: Lost Lake Cafe
directions: At the back of restaurant half
comment: Have to ask for code from staff

name: Elliott's hardware
directions: Far right in the back of the store.

name: Mexican mariachi grill
directions: In the back of the shop

name: OSU Tulsa Campus - Main Hall
directions: Second Floor, up the stairs and to the right.
comment: Just across from OSU Tulsa counseling center. Non students are welcome.

name: Arabica
directions: Straight to the back of the restaurant

name: Target
directions: Left from the entrance in the pharmacy

name: Rob's Ranch House
directions: To the left when you walk in, all the way down the stairs, if unsure ask staff
